<!-- -

provision = the initial value; 
constraint = the lowest possible utilization for triggering autoscaling; 
differences = the margin between two neighbor values, e.g. step = 5 would give 5MB, 10MB and 15MB etc; 
min = the minimum value; 
max = the maximum value; 
pre_to_max = the % threshold to trigger change of the max value; 
pre_of_max = the % extent to which the max value is changed; 
price_per_unit = the price per unit per hour for a service-instance.

(the unit for all cost/price in the file is per hour)

Please note that the min and max are dynamically updated. The lower bound is set to the maximum 
of a predefined value and the latest observed one. On the other hand, 
after the upper bound is set as an initial value, it is then dynamically adjusted 
based on the newly decided value and the latest observed one, i.e., it is increased by "pre_of_max"% if both
values converge to the upper bound larger than "pre_to_max"; likewise, it is decreased by "pre_of_max"% if both values diverge 
from the upper bound smaller than "pre_to_max".
-->

